// TEMPLATE: Handler Implementation Guide
//
// This file demonstrates the patterns for implementing handlers in this template.
// Copy and modify this file when creating new endpoints.
//
// Handler Structure:
// 1. Handlers are methods on the Handler struct (defined in baseHandler.go)
// 2. Method names match the operationId from openapi.yaml
// 3. All handlers follow the strict server interface pattern from oapi-codegen
//
// Common Patterns:
// - GET endpoints: Read data via repositories
// - POST endpoints: Create data via mutations
// - PUT/PATCH endpoints: Update data via mutations
// - DELETE endpoints: Delete data via mutations

